The customer service is amazing Debbie does a wonderful job directing her customers!

10/4/2021- Update: This place feeds off of first experience reviews they train their staff to ask for reviews on google, they even hand little papers to show you where to leave a review. When asked for explanation they said we periodically raise prices as stated in the terms and conditions so don't be fooled by the low prices you see now. < review>
The Good- Service is adequate, friendly staff
- Prices are attractive (but be-careful)
-Security is good
-Spaces are clean (wood inside is old)

The Bad- They're super aggressive and try to sell you everything! let me explain.....they hand you a lock when you first do the walk through and make it sound like its part of the deal but when you are about to sign the contract they charge you like $13.99 I believe for a lock you can get somewhere else for half the price, they make it sound like it's a requirement to buy their lock
- Also they almost force you to buy their boxes and supplies( super aggressive that intimidates you) I understand sales people are meant to upsell but sometimes they forget to remain professional when offering their products
- 1 Dollar moves you in? not true they charge you and admin fee of $25 dollars and also 61.67 in less than a month so shady for that one, also when they send you the bill the want you to pay one Month in advance for example I moved in on 10/24 and paid $25.00, got a bill right away for  $61.67 on 11/1 and on top of that they want you to pay  $229 in advance for 12/1-12/31...... so question is when I move out on 11/25 hopefully (would I get refunded back my 61.67??? why? because $25 moves you in for 30 days right? do the math
- Last but not least!- the Insurance.....this are their exact words when the insurance question pops up on their screen "You are required to purchase this insurance for your storage and this are the 3 options, which one would you like"........I'm scratching my head and replied " I'm not getting that I'll get my own.....they looked at each other and said ok just make sure you get it......again they force it into you( shady).....I called my home insurance when I got home and boom I actually get coverage without paying a penny more! I called them back and said " Would you like a copy of my policy? since you told me to make sure to get it? they said no......we don't need it just make sure you get it!.......one more thing! they absolutely force you to do a GOOGLE REVIEW right on the spot but I refused because I wanted to take my time and analyze my experience and do this later.......all those 5 star reviews they have probably because they force you to do it on the spot but I bet half of those are people who were not necessarily 5 star satisfied but since they are there next to you have no choice.......</review>

< Review>
I went to public storage looking for pricing. When I got there there were a few people in the office. Candice was the lady working by the Counter and she acknowledged my presence right away. She was very busy but very helpful, she did not make me feel rushed in any way. They were preparing for an auction at the time I can in and she invited me to stay for the auction. I did because I was curious. I was impressed with the way Candice knew the names of all the auction goers as well as the professions of the former owners of the storage units( which was helpfull to the auction goers. You would think she had eyes behind the back of her head, because she noticed that a renter needed help with something with her unit During the auction. She helprd her and was quickly back at the auction. As a business owner I could see how valuable she was to the company. Her boss was there (he was also very nice with a great sense of humor and he also knew the auction goers by name). You could see they had a great professional relationship, which I'm sure helps her be a great Employee. As I was leaving she called me by name and reminded me to call or come by with any questions. I will definitely be renting from this public storage.< /Review>

<pics>None</pics>< review>
I happened to be looking for a $1.00 storage unit. And before that, pretty much was having a bad day.. I located a PUBLIC STORAGE center in Fairfield Ca. On Beck street I explained to the associate, that  I was interested in one of the units as advertised on TV. Although there were none abailable, the associate at the desk , seeing that I wasnt having a good day. Proceeded to look up on
the computer to help me further. Out of all the things I had been mad about but was steadily saying ,something good has got to come out of this day. And it was, CANDICE , AN ASSOCIATE OF PUBLIC STORAGE, in Fairfield, Ca.  Talked to me and assured me that, she understood the situation, and was willing to give me a chance and regroup. Now not only was that exeptional service but it was above and beyond the call of duty. So I just wanted to thank them and her for standing up and honoring a T.V advertisement. That means nothing until you see., for yourself its not just marketing. But undersyanding as well.</review>

< text>
I came here looking for Dickies khaki pants for work. The store is clean, and appears to be organized but for the women's section many styles and sizes were misplaced. I ended up with a pair of mens khaki's, and the price on the tag said $31.99. They rang up at $32.99, and the staff member just told me the price is what is on the sign, regardless of the price on the actual item. I looked up the same pants on the Dickie's website- only $24.99 and they do refunds! This store only does exchanges, no refunds so there's really no reason for me to come back.< /text>

Best place ever. (Writing as a guy)

<Text>I have been coming to this office for close to 20 years and even though I am now a Senior citizen  and the office doesn't have medicare prices, I will continue coming to this dentist office.

The friendly atmosphere of ALL the staff at Dr. Dorfman's office is simply amazing... total concern and comfort for the patient starting with Sennette. They go above and beyond to make me feel comfortable.

I started with Dr. Dorfman who then put me in the very very capable hands of Dr. Gary Loosevelt, who has taken care of my dental needs for the last 19 years.

When I started with Dr. L., I let him know I didn't like dentists and told him in no uncertain terms what might happen if he hurt me while working on my mouth.  He smiled and turned his music back up and needless to say, he didn't hurt me then or since and I'm still going to him umpteen years later.

Dr. L.  has a very friendly, down-to-earth, tell-it-like-it-is demeanor.

Where for years I had a fear and phobia of dentists that kept me away from help way too long, not so with Dr. L.  I have no fear when I have to go see him.

No problems, no complaints.<//Text></record></dataset><record>

<user>106440345996550934423< /user><user_name>Alessandra Darouvar<//user_name>< date>
1539124540849</date>
< Rate>
5<//Rate>
< Review>
I mean I'm not gonna lie I was nervous about this whole process. I had A LOTTTTT of work that needed to be done and I was super nervous about choosing a Dr to do all of it - as it was going to be the one shot ($$) I had to fix everything.  A few friends recommended Dorfman and I must admit that I'm impressed.  He's everything I thought he'd be and more.  He has the same persona that he portrays on TV (bubbly and friendly) but I was so surprised to see how much he cared.  I've gotten a total of 14 veneers and 3 separate partial dentures.  He is a perfectionist (which I appreciate as an OCD person) and checks his work over and over until he is confident it's done properly.  His assistant is kick ass and made me feel comfortable every time I was in the chair.  And if you have done this amount of dental work you can imagine how long it took to accomplish everything I needed done.  Every single staff member that worked on me (ie: prepped me, took x-rays, took impressions, etc) was well versed on my case which made me feel good.  I wish I remembered their individual names but I don't.  I just know that they made me feel cared for.  They knew how important fixing my teeth was for me and they all supported me from diff angles.

I appreciated that I got to pick the "shade of white" and shapes/sizes of my veneers and dentures.  What was even more impressive was that the first version that came in for a "fitting" didn't look like the right shape I had originally asked for and I was nervous to say something but did and Dorfman couldn't have been more understanding and actually agreed with my opinion.  He sent everything back and re-ordered new ones - I REALLY appreciated that as my money only allows me to do this process once.   AND to top it all off I was scheduled to leave town and needed the final teeth to be put in before I left.  His office manager/staff had the laboratory drive it out (1.5 hours) to the office the day of my last appointment to make my deadline so I can leave town as scheduled.  Now that's what I call service!  I was SO touched that my case was as important to them as it is to me.

This office has been busy every time I've been there and it runs like a well oiled machine.  To me busy means good.  The staff is on their A game.  And I like all the high tech gadgets and machinery - looks like the latest stuff. Even though I probably paid a little more than I would have at another Dr I am beyond happy/satisfied with my decision and would do it again.  Fixing my teeth isn't like getting a haircut - it won't grow out.  I wasn't willing to go to the "cheaper option" just to save a few bucks.  This is work I will have in my mouth for the rest of my life and I needed to be sure it was going to get done perfectly!  WooooHoooooo!!! :)< /Review>

<rating>5<//rating>< Text>
I received excellent service from the staff at Aesthetic & General Dentistry. My positive experience started from the moment I made the appoinent with Christy over the phone.  Camila performed the Zoom! process in a timely, relaxed and efficient process.  The last time I had the Zoom! process was in 2004. That was an amazing experience as it made a signifcant improvement in the color of my teeth. But the Zoom! experience is not why I am posting this review.

Today's visit was first-class from the moment I checked in the office with Jennifer.  She was pleasant, attentive, and thourough with updating the paperwork process. She also asked me if I needed additional dental services.  As I was thinking of obtaining a second opinion regarding a cleaning and Xrays that were performed at a different office last week, I took her up on the offer.

She requested my Xrays from my previous dentist, and asked Dr. Doug Johnson to review them and perform an exam.  Upon meeting Dr. Johnson, I was impressed with his presense, confidence, and caring disposition. He was not rushed and offered to take a close look at my teeth, as he did not find and cavities on the Xrays (contrary to last week's diagnosis from my previous dentist).  He performed a thourough exam and confirmed that he did not see any signs of decay.

I am pleased to say that Dr. Johnson is my new dentist, as he saved me an unnecessary visit to have my first filling unnecessarily performed next week.

Aesthetic & General Dentistry provides an environment that removes the negative stereotypes associated with other dental offices and should be considered if you are looking for a new dental experience.< /Text>

< Rating>
5<//Rating>
<review>I moved from MI to CA in 2012 so naturally I had to find all new doctors for everything. My dentist in MI often bragged about his son becoming a dentist and a musician, and that he had moved to CA. My MI doctor was an excellent dentist and by whom I rated new dentists when in LA. I later learned the son went to work for Dr. Bill Dorfman in Century City's high rent district, famed dentist to the stars. For the first 3 years in LA, I went to several different dentists each of whom made my dental problems worse. None compared to the quality of work my MI dentist provided. I have numerous dental problems ie: loss of many teeth due to several accidents, crowns, partial, teeth shifting, bone loss, uneven jaw bone, the need to wear a custom night guard to save what's left, so my case is usually difficult for the average dentist. After several failed attempts by 'normal' dentists to get things right, I finally went to see Grant Loosvelt, DDS (my MI dentist son). He changed my life. Within 4 visits (which took other dentists near 4 years), he removed (with surgical perfection) an infected root that was left behind by another dentist when a tooth was pulled, and made a new custom mouth guard that fit like a glove. After the root was out and swelling down, my lower partial fit like never before, meaning I could eat normally again. Not only is he an excellent dentist, a master at his craft, he's also kind, gentle (more like a gentle giant - he's super tall), patient (I'm no picnic as a  patient), friendly and explained everything step by step, no surprises. I was blown away.

The only regret I had is that I didn't go to him sooner which would have saved me a lot of time, grief and pain. I will never go to a lesser dentist ever again. It's not worth it. Grant is a superior practitioner in his field of dentistry and aethetics. All his Dad's bragging was right on. Like father like son. And it was fun to be able to compare notes about MI.

And as a side note, I looked up his band ' The Disparrows' and listened to his music, awesome. And handsome as all hell to boot, not that that matters when one excels in their field, but it doesn't hurt either. Not bad on the eyes when you're nose to nose in a dentist chair! I have to go back soon for a cleaning (I have 2 of my own teeth left) which no doubt a hygienist will do but I have to say that this is the first time in my long 60 year history of dental problems that I'm looking forward to seeing my dentist. If going to the dentist scares you, like most people, give these guys a shot. After an experience with them and their very friendly staff, I doubt you'll ever be scared to go to the dentist again. 10 stars.</review><Time>1460150998560</Time>< Response>
